                  "motivation": "commenting",
                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p rend=\"align(right)\">\n                <hi rend=\"underline\">Tal. 2.</hi>\n            </p>\n            <p>\n                <add>שלא היה בלבי להטיב לאיש פלוני כי אמרו להרע לפלוני ואח\"כ התפעל או בא אחר\n                    בעדו</add>\n            </p>\n            <p>God is the most perfect existence, therefore <add>במענה רק אל המלך והתחנו לפניו והמלך\n                    חשוב ממחשבותו – עוד לא כן הקב\"ה כי לא</add><lb/> no <sic>altaretion</sic> can be\n                thought in his divine Character for<lb/> every <sic>altaretion</sic> is a proof of\n                imperfection.</p>\n            <p>By that prim we learn:</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">a Hymns and praises so the Living God shall be the chief<lb/> apart,\n                prayers of supplication and respontenie<add>?</add> the second and<lb/>\n                <sic>smaler</sic> part of our liturgy. The Talmud itself is of this meaning</p>\n            <p>\n                <add>במחשבותיו משבותנו כי אנחנו בעל שינוי להסיר ממחשבתו, והדרך ילכו אור באמונתו\n                    הקב\"ה</add>\n            </p>\n            <p>Purer words in that reference said the orthodox <add>שומע תפילות כל פה הוא דוקא\n                    כשמתפלל שינה את עצמו במחשבה בדיבור ובמעשה</add>.</p>\n            <p>After reverend gentleman said the opinion of the Talmud, he<lb/> expressed his view\n                about it:</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">The chief precept of our Religion is: to be holy, that<lb/> is: so\n                love God, for this is holiness. Inferior so this<lb/> precept is: to acknowledge\n                God, expressed in the first command<lb/>ment of the revelation. If we acknowledge\n                God, we love him<lb/> and are holy. Our Holy Thora is the guide to the summit<lb/>\n                of this divine Dea<add>?</add>. Philanthropy, kindness and mercy to every<lb/>\n                creature both living and lifeless, rectitude for the whole human<lb/> race, a\n                powerful dominion above ourselves as well as above nature are<lb/> the ways, which\n                our Thora teaches us, to acknowledge the invisible<lb/> Deity by his divine\n                attributes. Be as kind and <sic>mercyful</sic> as our<lb/> Thora will it, thus Gods\n                benevolence is displayed unto you &amp;<lb/> but <del>who</del> total you will never\n                acknowledge him <add>ודהו שומע תפילה וגו'</add><lb/> But yet a way shows no us our\n                Thora to aim this holy end, and this<lb/> way is the prayer, and therefore is it the\n                most perfect services</p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p39z90z3v/canvas/p1"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
