              "items": [
                {
                  "id": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p39z90z3v/manifest/annotation/p4",
                  "type": "Annotation",
                  "motivation": "commenting",
                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p>(I am afraid the multitude of <add>חובת הלבבות שער היחוד</add> and the sing-sing of\n                    <add>ומת כל אליענו הקרוב עלינו בכל קראנו אליו</add> and<lb/>\n                <add>שבת יב</add> shall bad suffer by that)</p>\n            <p>Now, my orthodox brother, here are the principles<lb/> of <persName>Rabbi\n                    Wise</persName>, according which the new<lb/> liturgy shall appear. Here is a\n                mount of<lb/> truths, of Information and conviction, there is<lb/> Tara and\n                Philosophy going hand in hand. What<lb/> can in right be said against those truths?\n                nothing,<lb/> but so wish the whole liturgy may be to consequence<lb/> of those\n                principles, that all the congregations of<lb/>\n                <placeName>Israel</placeName> may adore our God according to those principles,<lb/>\n                and the new liturgy may be successful to unite<lb/>\n                <placeName>Israel</placeName> in <placeName>Amerika</placeName> into one great\n                body</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">\n                <add>ואלו הן פרקליטיו של אדם תשובה ומעשים טובים</add>\n            </p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(2)\">I am <persName role=\"author\">Joseph</persName> your brother</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(6)\"><sic><addressee>Rev. Mr. Elisser</addressee></sic>!</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">Dear Sir!</p>\n            <p>I send you those ripe fruits of <persName>Rabbi Wise</persName>, that<lb/> the\n                reading people may know, what we have to expect<lb/> of this energiral<add>?</add>\n                doctor, for it is more than sure, that<lb/> he will give the <sic>impuls</sic> to\n                great motions by his active<lb/> spirit and multitude of sciences. He is powerful in\n                the province<lb/> of speaking as sublime in his <add>?</add>eas. I have mistakes\n                in<lb/> my writing, but I am in haste and pray you to correct it.<lb/> Some\n                    <sic>supscribers</sic> of the <sic>occident</sic> I gathered, and next I\n                will<lb/> send you the money.</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(10)\">Dear Sir</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(11)\">I am yours</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(10)\">\n                <persName role=\"author\">LJ</persName>\n            </p>\n            <p>Perhaps you can find place for those lines<lb/> in your Journal of this month.</p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p39z90z3v/canvas/p4"
                }
