                  "type": "Annotation",
                  "motivation": "commenting",
                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p rend=\"align(center)\">\n                <addressee>John Samuel Esq.</addressee>\n            </p>\n            <p>Dear Sir!</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">Being in possession of your<lb/> favor of the <date>12.</date>\n                inst., I am sorry that I<lb/> cannot serve you; as usually I have not preserved<lb/>\n                the articles on Jurisprudence. I am very lazy in<lb/> this respect.</p>\n            <p>Please to inform the judge, that he can find<lb/> a historical development of the\n                subject in the<lb/> appendices to each period of my “History &amp;c,<lb/> which will\n                be continued in each of the following<lb/> volumes.</p>\n            <p>I took the liberty of sending to you ten copies<lb/> of the first volume of my\n                History to supply<lb/> you and your friends; since I cannot immediately<lb/> send an\n                agent to distribute them.</p>\n            <p>Please deposit some copies in a bookstore which<lb/> you think most fit together with\n                one of the<lb/> annexed circulars. I sell to bookstores for<lb/> $1,50 per copy.</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(7)\">Most Respectfully</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(8)\">Yours</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(8)\">\n                <persName role=\"author\">Isaac M. Wise</persName>\n            </p>\n            <p><placeName>Albany</placeName>\n                <date>December 14: 1853</date>.</p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p39z90z3v/canvas/p6"
                }
