              "items": [
                {
                  "id": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p39z90z3v/manifest/annotation/p7",
                  "type": "Annotation",
                  "motivation": "commenting",
                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p>a hundred times, without ever to reason or to think on<lb/> any one subject;\n                therefore I bid a farewell to <sic>jewish</sic><lb/> literature, to\n                    <sic>jewish</sic> quarrels, to <sic>jewish</sic> struggles, and<lb/> threw my\n                whole force upon profane sciences, and I<lb/> shall in a month or two try my fortune\n                as a<lb/> philosophic author, <hi rend=\"underline\">an Essay on immortality</hi>\n                with<lb/> physical evidences I have nearly finished, and it<lb/> will be published\n                right of; if I am not more<lb/> fortunate as a philosophical author than I was<lb/>\n                as a rabbi, I shall compile spelling books for<lb/> little children or till the\n                ground to earn a living and<lb/> let humbuggers be ministers, teachers,\n                professors,<lb/> authors or whatever they chose to be. This may excuse<lb/> for not\n                having done what I <sic>promissed</sic>.</p>\n            <p>You remembered me or the school of <placeName>Padua</placeName>, and<lb/> that is the\n                most serious wound in my heart, which<lb/> you could touch; first all the proud\n                hopes, which<lb/> I there entertained, which I see now fade away came<lb/> some\n                more, in my mind; secondly it grieves me<lb/> very much, that our\n                    <sic>american</sic>\n                <sic>jews</sic> could not come<lb/> up to the great idea of establishing such a\n                school;<lb/> and third, it grieves me seriously to know, what<lb/> pure Judaism I\n                studied there and what a corrupted<lb/> one we have here.</p>\n            <p>I wish you give my best respect to your mother<lb/> and to your father.</p>\n            <p>I shall be happy to serve you in any way.</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(6)\">Faithfully</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(5)\">Your obd't s't</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(6)\">\n                <persName role=\"author\">Dr Wise</persName>\n            </p>\n            <p>\n                <addressee>John Samuel Esq.</addressee>\n                <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>\n            </p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p39z90z3v/canvas/p7"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
