          "annotations": [
            {
              "id": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p39z90z3v/canvas/p9/annopage",
              "type": "AnnotationPage",
              "items": [
                {
                  "id": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p39z90z3v/manifest/annotation/p9",
                  "type": "Annotation",
                  "motivation": "commenting",
                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p>I hope to give to the world a history of our nation, which<lb/> will fully show the\n                important position of <placeName>Israel</placeName> among the<lb/> nations. You see,\n                my dear sir, that I did not yet think how<lb/> to publish it, as I was not sure of\n                success; but now I<lb/> have made my plan to this effect. As soon as the number<lb/>\n                of subscribers is important enough, I shall publish the<lb/> first volume reaching\n                to the destruction of the first<lb/> temple. I shall first offer the business to\n                    <persName>Mr. Hart</persName> of<lb/>\n                <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>; because he, being an Israelite, feels more\n                    in<add>?</add><lb/> in the matter than other publishers. If we cannot agree<lb/>\n                on the terms for I have about $1500,00 expenses for books<lb/> necessary to the\n                purpose—then I thought of going to <persName>Harpen</persName><lb/> or another\n                publisher. If I can agree with none I publish<lb/> it myself for my subscribers\n                only; for them, after the work<lb/> will be completed, I am sure every publisher\n                will buy the<lb/> copy right. It will remain a standard work for the next<lb/> 25\n                years. This is my intention, and I see in your letter,<lb/> it will meet with your\n                approbation.</p>\n            <p>I wish, you would be kind enough, to let me have your<lb/> corrections on the\n                Jurisprudence of the Israelites.</p>\n            <p>Please to accept of my assurance of my best respect.</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(4)\">Truly Yours</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(5)\">\n                <persName role=\"author\">Dr Wise</persName>\n            </p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p39z90z3v/canvas/p9"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
