                  "motivation": "commenting",
                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p rend=\"align(right)\"><placeName>Albany</placeName>, <date>March 25. 1853</date></p>\n            <p rend=\"align(center)\">To <addressee>John Samuel Esq.</addressee>\n                <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName></p>\n            <p>Dear Sir</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">Your favor of the <date>24.</date> inst. was <sic>duely</sic>\n                received, and<lb/> I take of this early opportunity to thank you for your\n                kindness<lb/> which you manifest in the interest taken in my intended<lb/>\n                publication. Permit me, dear sir, to give you a short<lb/> history of my history,\n                and you will find, that your<lb/> suggestions are really welcome to me.</p>\n            <p>I felt for years the necessity of having a complete and<lb/> unfalsified account of\n                our nation in the English language,<lb/> wherefore I commenced translating\n                    <persName>Jost's</persName> history of the<lb/> Israelites; after I was done\n                nearly half with the work<lb/> I notified my attention to the public; but the\n                opposition<lb/> against this work was great both here and in\n                    <placeName>Germany</placeName>.<lb/>\n                <persName>Dr. Frankel</persName> of <placeName>Dresden</placeName>, and\n                    <persName>Dr. Sachs</persName> of <placeName>Berlin</placeName>, as<lb/> well as\n                    <persName>Dr. Raphael</persName> of <placeName>New York</placeName> and others\n                were<lb/> greatly opposed to the work; because, they say, <persName>Dr.\n                    Jost</persName><lb/> did not write in the interest of Jews, but to obtain a<lb/>\n                professorship. I know this, but I had not the moral<lb/> courage to undertake the\n                composition of an original<lb/> work. My friends in <placeName>Germany</placeName>,\n                and especially <persName>Dr.<lb/> Frankel</persName> urged the matter upon me; my\n                friends here also<lb/> wanted me to try, but every one doubted, that the work</p>\n        </body>\n    </text>\n</TEI>"
                  },
